Management Groups:  Groups multiple subscriptions for easier management.
   └── Subscriptions:  For billing purpose-Has no of resource groups. Ex: devSub, testSub.
        └── Resource Groups:  Group of resources. Ex: V-Net, VM's, Storage etc... as one group.
              └── Resources:  Actual resources. Ex: VM's etc...


When you create Azure account, you get:
Tenant-ID
  └──  Subscriptions
         └──  Resource Groups
                └──  Resources
Resource Manager: Who creates the resource.
-- User request for some resource---request goes to Resource Manager----Resource Manager provides resource.
